rComments: An amazing prof, very kind and tries to ensure everyone gets the highest possible grade. Although it was a seminar course, he gives little assignments so the quieter ones can boost their mark under "class participation". If you want an easy, interesting course with an amazing prof, this is the one.

This class was amazing. He is a great prof who really only cares about great discussion and learning from the students. As long you really care and try you will do well in the class. He's very open and honest and the content is really fun. Would highly recommend.

Prof. MacDonald is pretty old school in the best of ways. This class had absolutely no slides, and was all about the discussions on our readings and integrating it into current pop-culture themes.  If you enjoy readings, writing journals and a research essay, put in the work, and care, you will find he is the most easiest of markers.  Educational!

Prof MacDonald is very enthusiastic and well spoken.  He posted the marks of major components of the course a few days before the exam.  I was in for a surprise.  If you aren't good at writing, do not take his course.  The mark was not worth the effort.
